The effect on the superconducting state by the external magnetic field is best exposed from the field theory by following a string of approximations summarized in Fig.~\ref{approxladder}.  The simplifications begin with BCS and GL to reduce the equations and fields to the minimum number of variables needed to describe each Cooper pair.  The resulting Usadel's equations depend only on the center of mass position and energy of each pair \cite{usadelPRL70}.   

